blocks.description:
blocks
The blocks that drop loot
   
List of BlockDatas (Objects)

    
* Default Value is an empty list
* At least one entry must be defined, or just remove this list.

exactBlocks.description:
exactBlocks
If exact blocks is set to true, minecraft:barrel[axis=x] will only drop for that axis. When exact is false (default) any barrel will drop the defined drops.
   
Boolean

    
* Default Value is a default object (create this object to see default properties)

drops.description:
drops
Add in specific items to drop
   
List of Loots (Objects)

    
* Default Value is an empty list
* At least one entry must be defined, or just remove this list.

skipParents.description:
skipParents
If this is in a biome, setting skipParents to true will ignore the drops in the region and dimension for this block type. The default (false) will allow all three nodes to fire and add to a list of drops.
   
Boolean

    
* Default Value is a default object (create this object to see default properties)

replaceVanillaDrops.description:
replaceVanillaDrops
Removes the default vanilla block drops and only drops the given items & any parent loot tables specified for this block type.
   
Boolean

    
* Default Value is a default object (create this object to see default properties)

preprocessors.description:
preprocessors
Preprocess this object in-memory when it's loaded, run scripts using the variable 'Iris.getPreprocessorObject()' and modify properties about this object before it's used.
   
List<Script>

    
* Default Value is an empty list
* At least one entry must be defined, or just remove this list.
Must be a valid Script (use ctrl+space for auto complete!)

weight.description:
weight
The weight is used when this block data is inside of a list of blockdata. A weight of two is just as if you placed two of the same block data values in the same list making it more common when randomly picked.
   
Integer

    
* Default Value is 1
* Minimum allowed is 1
* Maximum allowed is 1000

anyOf.description: Represents an attribute modifier for an item or an entity. This allows you to create modifications to basic game attributes such as MAX_HEALTH or ARMOR_VALUE.

attribute.description:
attribute
The Attribute type. This type is pulled from the game attributes. Zombie & Horse attributes will not work on non-zombie/horse entities.
Using an attribute on an item will have affects when held, or worn. There is no way to specify further granularity as the game picks this depending on the item type.
   
Attribute

Must be a valid Attribute (use ctrl+space for auto complete!)

name.description:
name
The Attribute Name is used internally only for the game. This value should be unique to all other attributes applied to this item/entity. It is not shown in game.
   
Text

    
* Default Value is 
* Minimum Length allowed is 2

operation.description:
operation
The application operation (add number is default). Add Number adds to the default value. 
Add scalar_1 will multiply by 1 for example if the health is 20 and you multiply_scalar_1 by 0.5, the health will result in 30, not 10. Use negative values to achieve that.
   
Operation

    
* Default Value is a default object (create this object to see default properties)
Must be a valid Operation (use ctrl+space for auto complete!)

minAmount.description:
minAmount

maxAmount.description:
maxAmount

Number

chance.description:
chance
The chance that this attribute is applied (0 to 1). If the chance is 0.5 (50%), then Iris will only apply this attribute 50% of the time.
   
Number

    
* Default Value is 1.0
* Minimum allowed is 0.0
* Maximum allowed is 1.0
